      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation inputs independently reviewed by a second analyst; boundary conditions and material assignments documented and checked against test protocol.",
      "rationale": "A second senior analyst independently reconstructed boundary conditions from the ASTM F1717 test protocol and compared against the simulation setup. No discrepancies were identified. Material assignments were cross-checked against the DePuy Synthes material datasheet. Required level achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum elastic-plastic constitutive model with isotropic hardening validated against uniaxial coupon data; contact formulation verified for frictionless and frictional cases.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening model calibrated to Ti-6Al-4V coupon stress-strain data (R² = 0.998). Augmented Lagrange contact formulation was verified against closed-form Hertzian solutions. Model form is appropriate for the compression-bending COU; required level achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from lot-specific coupon testing; geometric inputs derived from CMM measurements of production screws; uncertainty bounds quantified for all primary inputs.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus (114 GPa ± 2.1%), yield strength (880 MPa ± 1.8%), and tangent modulus quantified from lot-specific tensile coupons. Screw geometry verified via CMM on three production units; dimensional variation < 0.02 mm. Input uncertainty propagated via Monte Carlo (n=1000). Required level achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N ≥ 10 test constructs from production lots; lot traceability documented; dimensional inspection confirms constructs within drawing tolerances.",
      "rationale": "N=11 constructs assembled from production-released components (lot numbers on file). CMM inspection confirmed all critical dimensions within ±0.05 mm of nominal. Two independent laboratories contributed specimens to assess inter-lab variability. Required level achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of clinically relevant loading scenarios including at minimum two load levels and two construct configurations.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted exclusively under the standard ASTM F1717 single-level compression-bending configuration at a single crosshead displacement rate (5 mm/min). No variation in load level, offset distance, or construct configuration was explored. Although the standard protocol was followed rigorously, the absence of parametric variation in test conditions means the validation evidence does not cover the full envelope of clinically relevant scenarios. Achieved level (2) falls below the required level (3). This shortfall was noted by the assessment team but judged acceptable given the strong agreement between FEA and experiment across all three QoIs and the conservative nature of the single worst-case loading condition."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation inputs match test conditions within stated uncertainty bounds; any deviations are documented and their impact on QoIs assessed.",
      "rationale": "Applied displacement boundary conditions in the FEA replicate the test machine crosshead displacement. Fixture geometry was measured and incorporated into the model. The only deviation — a 0.3° angular misalignment observed in Lab 2 — was modeled explicitly and found to change predicted stiffness by 0.4%, within uncertainty bounds. Required level achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric E/uval < 1.96 for all QoIs; relative error < 10% for all QoIs; statistical equivalence demonstrated.",
      "rationale": "All three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) satisfy E/uval < 1.96 and relative error < 2.1%. Combined validation uncertainty uval incorporates experimental repeatability (inter-lab and intra-lab), input parameter uncertainty, and numerical error. The validation metric framework follows ASME V&V 10-2006 Section 5. Required level achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly correspond to the regulatory submission metrics and clinical failure modes; traceability from QoI to design requirement documented.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs specified in the FDA guidance for ASTM F1717 submissions. Each QoI maps directly to a design requirement in the device DHF. Traceability matrix on file. Required level achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities use production-equivalent hardware, clinically representative loading, and the same model configuration as the COU submission model.",
      "rationale": "Validation constructs used production-released screws and rods identical to those in the 510(k) submission. The FEA model used for validation is configuration-controlled and identical to the submission model. Loading replicates the standard regulatory test. Validation activities are directly relevant to the COU; required level achieved."
    }
